LSE Bond Data May Be Unavailable as Computers Change, FT Says

-- B y   J a c k   J o r d a n
-- 
2011-03-12T08:46:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-12/lse-bond-data-may-be-unavailable-as-computers-change-ft-says.html
Some real-time bond prices may be
unavailable from  London Stock Exchange Group Plc (LSE)  as the exchange
changes its trading-platform system, the Financial Times
reported, citing comments made by LSE Group.  Some investors have been unable to see retail bond-market
data since Feb. 14, when the exchange started using its new
trading platform, MillenniumIT, LSE Group said, the newspaper
reported. The problem should be resolved in due course, the
company said, the FT reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jack Jordan in  London  at 
 jjordan22@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 